metadata.name: Manu #127
metadata.description:
Manu
---------------

A collector-led exploration of minimalist imperfect line work.

Outputs are generated from a combination of the minter's address, their choice from one of 50 seeds, and options to adjust how the generated surface is presented.

Palettes are named after native New Zealand birds and range from the subdued to the colorful.

There are no especially rare traits so mint what you love :)

---------------

Controls:
S - Export as png
H - Toggle high resolution

metadata.name: Maelstrom #95
metadata.description:
Ever-drawing cosmic storm, swallowing all that is bright into effervescent particles only to collapse on itself. Like a fire hungry for oxygen, chaos takes center stage for a fraction of what we called time, then gracefully settles into blaze and dust. From hereafter, a nascent star may dance.

When I think about a pause in creation after some time, I thought of this. Like an effervescent tablet touching by the water, sometimes a drive just dissolves into indifference. But rather than trying to lit a wet log, it would be better to be burnt by something else.

------------
Press [s] to save captured image
------------
It may take a few seconds to render, depending on the device.
works better with chrome

created using WEBGL on p5.js
dirbots - Aug23

metadata.name: ecolog√≠as - A #1896
metadata.description:
ecolog√≠as - A

lines are a metaphor for the communication all species engage in. We as humans have a need to leave traces - stories - that others can read and learn from. What will be the traces machines want to leave? This piece employs sinusoidal signals drawn with lines as a simple metaphor for every trace and every language, for every message and every communication.

ecolog√≠as-A is an entity that is part of a broader ecology. Released on occasion of the show "Unbound - Ecology in the Age of Machines" at Unit London. The data generated by this entity is read by a different piece minted on Ethereum, creating a link between Tezos and Ethereum, a metaphor for an ecology of blockchains.

it shares a common element with two other works released on fxhash: ecolog√≠as B and ecolog√≠as C, all of them contributing data to aforementioned pieces.

read more at https://www.iillucid.com/ecologias

15% of primary sales are donated to institutions working towards improving biodiversity and environmental efforts.

Marcelo Soria-Rodr√≠guez, @msoriaro

metadata.name: Momentum #191
metadata.description:
In our new project, we explore the possibilities and tools of generative art. This time we were interested in the aesthetics of particles. When static turns into movement, and the predicted composition becomes spontaneous - the experiment continues.
This project was created with P5.js.
March 2023.
Press 'S' to save a PNG file.

metadata.name: ecolog√≠as - B #435
metadata.description:
ecolog√≠as - B

water is the medium where life first appeared in our planet. Water is also indispensable for the continuation of the life that emerged from - and with - it. The advent of AI species and their introduction into society is a new form of cambrian explosion. What is their medium? What is their water? How scarce and precious will it be for them? AI entities are not foreign to human resource necessities, though. The water that is essential to our human life will also be so for machines, as their energy still depends on our natural resources. Therefore, the ecologies of humans and machines will have, at least, the same elements as the ecologies of humans. AIs may help us reach better balances, only if we employ them to do so and if we teach them to help us.

metadata.name: Teppich #202
metadata.description:
The German term for rug, carpet, or tapestry; I‚Äôve chosen this translation specifically because of its multiple meanings, what originally was a texture study of fabric became more recognizable as a rug. There are imperfections in the stitching, some bits of the underlay and adjacent colors bleeding into others. This name accurately captures both the intention and result of this piece.

Each Teppich can take anywhere from 15-60s to render depending on hardware. Please be patient and refer to your loading spinner for a taste.

Export to a 4500x3600 png with ‚Äôs‚Äô for up to A3 printing or a jpg with ‚Äòj‚Äô for a smaller file size.

metadata.name: Act One #6
metadata.description:
Act One, where the mannequin says ‚Äútake me home and I will dance for you forever‚Äù.

This work is an exploration of using motion capture data to create digital paintings, and a little belated birthday ballet for #fxhashturnsone. 
20% of primary sales are donated to Three.js.
 
Keyboard Controls:
[P] Play / pause the dance. By default the dance is paused after a few seconds to render a painting.
[S] Save the current view (live mode).
[V] Capture a short webm video (live mode).

Mouse Controls (while dancing): 
[left drag] Rotate
[scroll] Zoom
[right drag] Pan
[right click] Save image

Best viewed in a desktop browser. The output may be different from the preview image if your frame rate is low, reducing the size of the browser window can help improve the frame rate.

Made using Three.js, canvas API and WebGL2.
The 3D model is based on https://sketchfab.com/3d-models/mannequin-dances-ballet-a24678a81a6f4b6d8f8ba0eb1a78e58b, using motion capture data from dancedb.eu. 
Test in Chrome v107.0.5304.107 and Safari v16.1.
License: CC BY-NC-SA 2.0

Created by elsif, 2022.11.

metadata.name: Polka #64
metadata.description:
'Polka' combines two of the simplist forms in geometry (the rectangle and the circle) with a bright 'popping' color palette to create bold, abstract, geometric designs.

Creation: A series of colorfully illustrated layers (containing transparent regions) are stacked. Each layer is selected at random from several options. This means that each output is a unique artwork.

To download a 1500x2000px PNG:
Click/tap 'open', then click/tap the image to make a "Download image" button appear.

Inspired by the doilies at grandma's house.

metadata.name: ecolog√≠as - A #1633
metadata.description:
ecolog√≠as - A

lines are a metaphor for the communication all species engage in. We as humans have a need to leave traces - stories - that others can read and learn from. What will be the traces machines want to leave? This piece employs sinusoidal signals drawn with lines as a simple metaphor for every trace and every language, for every message and every communication.

ecolog√≠as-A is an entity that is part of a broader ecology. Released on occasion of the show "Unbound - Ecology in the Age of Machines" at Unit London. The data generated by this entity is read by a different piece minted on Ethereum, creating a link between Tezos and Ethereum, a metaphor for an ecology of blockchains.

it shares a common element with two other works released on fxhash: ecolog√≠as B and ecolog√≠as C, all of them contributing data to aforementioned pieces.

read more at https://www.iillucid.com/ecologias

15% of primary sales are donated to institutions working towards improving biodiversity and environmental efforts.
